DIGEST: SOUTH GATE; 
BLOOD DONATIONS ACCEPTED MONTHLY AT RED CROSS OFFICE 
Residents may give blood at the American Red Cross Service Center, 9200 State 
St., South Gate, from 2:45 to 7:30 p.m. on the last Friday of every month. 
Donors must be healthy and 17 or older. Appointments can be made by calling the 
Red Cross at 739-5290. 
More than 200 hospitals in Los Angeles and Orange counties are supplied by Red 
Cross Blood Services. The short shelf life of blood products, anywhere from a 
few hours to 42 days, makes continual giving necessary. 
